"title": "5260: coinage",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5260: coinage",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Coinage was not used until the late 7th century B.C. Weights of silver and gold were earlier used as “currency”. By the later exile a variety of minted coinage, made from gold, silver, bronze or copper, gradually replaced the method of reckoning currency by weighing out precious metals. Israelite, Persian, Greek and Roman coins are mentioned in Scripture.</p>\n<h2>The talent</h2>\n<h3>A unit of weight</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs10:14\">1KI 10:14</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr9:13\">2CH 9:13</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod38:25\">EXO 38:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod38:29\">EXO 38:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs9:28\">1KI 9:28</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr8:18\">2CH 8:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs10:10\">1KI 10:10</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr9:9\">2CH 9:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr22:14\">1CH 22:14</a></p>\n<h3>A weight for precious metals used as currency</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs20:39\">1KI 20:39</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs9:14\">1KI 9:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs16:24\">1KI 16:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs5:5\">2KI 5:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs5:22-2Kgs5:23\">2KI 5:22–5:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs15:19\">2KI 15:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs18:14\">2KI 18:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:33\">2KI 23:33</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr36:3\">2CH 36:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr19:6\">1CH 19:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr25:6\">2CH 25:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr25:9\">2CH 25:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr27:5\">2CH 27:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth3:9\">EST 3:9</a></p>\n<h3>Adopted as the name of a coin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:23-Matt18:35\">MAT 18:23–18:35</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:14-Matt25:30\">MAT 25:14–25:30</a></p>\n<h2>The shekel</h2>\n<h3>Its value</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek45:10-Ezek45:12\">EZK 45:10–45:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:13\">EXO 30:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod38:25-Exod38:26\">EXO 38:25–38:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev27:25\">LEV 27:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num3:46-Num3:47\">NUM 3:46–3:47</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num18:16\">NUM 18:16</a></p>\n<h3>Used as currency</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa7:23\">ISA 7:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:15\">EXO 30:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev27:1-Lev27:8\">LEV 27:1–27:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut22:19\">DEU 22:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut22:29\">DEU 22:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg9:4\">JDG 9:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg16:5\">JDG 16:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg17:10\">JDG 17:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam13:21\">1SA 13:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam18:12\">2SA 18:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs6:25\">2KI 6:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs7:1\">2KI 7:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs7:16\">2KI 7:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs7:18\">2KI 7:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr21:25\">1CH 21:25</a> <em>David's payment for the threshing-floor as the temple site</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr1:17\">2CH 1:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh5:15\">NEH 5:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh10:32\">NEH 10:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer32:9\">JER 32:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos3:2\">HOS 3:2</a></p>\n<h2>The denarius</h2>\n<h3>Referred to in Jesus Christ's parables</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:1-Matt20:16\">MAT 20:1–20:16</a></strong> <em>One denarius was the average worker's daily wage.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:21-Matt18:35\">MAT 18:21–18:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:41-Luke7:47\">LUK 7:41–7:47</a></p>\n<h3>As the unit for the payment of taxes to Rome</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:15-Matt22:21\">MAT 22:15–22:21</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:13-Mark12:17\">MRK 12:13–12:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:20-Luke20:26\">LUK 20:20–20:26</a></p>\n<h2>The penny</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:29\">MAT 10:29</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:6\">LUK 12:6</a> <em>The “penny” was not a coin in use in biblical times, but the term is employed in the NIV for two different copper coins, the “assarion” and the “quadrans”, which were of relatively little value.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:25-Matt5:26\">MAT 5:25–5:26</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:58-Luke12:59\">LUK 12:58–12:59</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:42\">MRK 12:42</a></p>\n<h2>The gerah</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev27:25\">LEV 27:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:13\">EXO 30:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num3:47\">NUM 3:47</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num18:16\">NUM 18:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek45:12\">EZK 45:12</a></p>\n<h2>The drachma</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:19\">ACT 19:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra2:69\">EZR 2:69</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh7:70-Neh7:72\">NEH 7:70–7:72</a></p>\n<h2>The four-drachma coin</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:24-Matt17:27\">MAT 17:24–17:27</a></strong></p>\n<h2>The daric</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr29:7\">1CH 29:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra8:27\">EZR 8:27</a></p>\n<h2>Unnamed coins</h2>\n<h3>General references to coins</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John2:13-John2:16\">JHN 2:13–2:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:6\">MAT 27:6</a></p>\n<h3>Silver coins</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:14-Matt26:15\">MAT 26:14–26:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:3-Matt27:10\">MAT 27:3–27:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech11:12-Zech11:13\">ZEC 11:12–11:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:30-Luke10:35\">LUK 10:30–10:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:8-Luke15:10\">LUK 15:8–15:10</a> <em>Although translated simply as “silver coins”, it is the “drachma” which is referred to here.</em></p>\n<h3>Copper coins</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:41-Mark12:42\">MRK 12:41–12:42</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:1-Luke21:2\">LUK 21:1–21:2</a> <em>The Greek coin “lepton” is translated as “copper coin” in these passages.</em></p>",
